---
import MemberLayout from "../../layouts/MemberLayout.astro";
const version = Date.now();

const frontmatter = {
  title: "Manage Your Public Profile | Wikimint Marketing Platform",
  description: "Update your Wikimint public profile by managing your description, website, social links, recommended resources, and profile information. Keep your profile current, improve visitor engagement, and manage your online presence from one place.",
  image: "/assets/images/others/manage-public-profile-wikimint-marketing-platform.webp",
  tags: ["about", "business", "finance"],
  author: "Wikimint Team",
  disableAds: true,
};
---

<MemberLayout frontmatter={frontmatter}>

<div class="mo mb-10">
<div id="profileForm">

    <div class="space-y-8">

        <!-- Basic Information -->
        <fieldset>
        <legend>Basic Information</legend>

            
    
                <div class="space-y-5">
    
                    <div>
    
                        <label class="block mb-2 font-medium">
    
                            User ID
    
                        </label>
    
                        <input
                            id="userid"
                            type="text"
                            readonly disabled
                            class="w-full px-4 py-1 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300"
                        >
    
                    </div>
    
                    <div>
    
                        <label class="block mb-2 font-medium">
    
                            Email
    
                        </label>
    
                        <input
                            id="email"
                            type="email"
                            readonly disabled
                            class="w-full px-4 py-1 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300"
                        >
    
                    </div>
    
                    <div>
    
                        <label class="block mb-2 font-medium">
    
                            Full Name <span class="text-red-500">*</span>
    
                        </label>
    
                        <input
                            id="name"
                            maxlength="100"
                            class="w-full px-4 py-1 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300"
                        >
    
                    </div>
    
                    <div>
    
                        <label class="block mb-2 font-medium">
    
                            Professional Headline
    
                        </label>
    
                        <input
                            id="headline"
                            maxlength="100"
                            placeholder="Web Developer | SEO Specialist"
                            class="w-full px-4 py-1 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300"
                        >
    
                    </div>
    
                </div>
    

    
        </fieldset>
        <!-- About Me -->

<fieldset>
<legend>About Me</legend>

    <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-6">

      

        <span
            id="descriptionCount"
            class="text-sm text-gray-500"
        >
            0 / 1000
        </span>

    </div>

    <textarea
        id="description"
        rows="8"
        maxlength="1000"
        placeholder="Tell visitors about yourself, your experience, expertise and what you do."
        class="w-full border border-gray-300 bg-gray-50 px-4 py-3 resize-y"
    ></textarea>

    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-500">

        Plain text only. HTML and links are not allowed.

    </p>

</fieldset>



<fieldset>
    <legend>Profile Visibility</legend>
    <div class="form-group">

        <label for="profile_visibility">
    
            Profile Visibility
    
        </label>
    
        <select id="profile_visibility" class="px-4 py-1 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300">
    
            <option value="public">
    
                Public
    
            </option>
    
            <option value="private">
    
                Private
    
            </option>
    
        </select>
    
        <small>
    
            <p>Public profiles are visible to visitors. Private profiles are hidden.</p>
    
        </small>
    
    </div>
    </fieldset>




<fieldset>
    <legend>Professional Category</legend>
    <div class="form-group">

        <label for="profile_category">
    
            Professional Category
    
        </label>
    
        <select id="profile_category"  class="px-4 py-1 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300">
    
            <option value="professional">Professional</option>
    
            <option value="entrepreneur">Entrepreneur</option>
    
            <option value="freelancer">Freelancer</option>
    
            <option value="business-owner">Business Owner</option>
    
            <option value="digital-marketer">Digital Marketer</option>
    
            <option value="software-developer">Software Developer</option>
    
            <option value="consultant">Consultant</option>
    
            <option value="content-creator">Content Creator</option>
    
            <option value="educator">Educator / Trainer</option>
    
            <option value="creative-professional">Creative Professional</option>
    
        </select>
    
    </div>
    
    </fieldset>



<!-- Business Information -->
<fieldset>
<legend>Business Information</legend>

    <div class="space-y-6">

        <!-- Company -->

        <div>

            <label class="block mb-2 font-medium">

                Company

            </label>

            <input
                id="company"
                type="text"
                maxlength="100"
                placeholder="Company or Business Name"
                class="w-full px-4 py-1 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300"
            >

        </div>

        <!-- Website -->

        <div>

            <label class="block mb-2 font-medium">

                Website

            </label>

            <input
                id="website"
                type="url"
                maxlength="200"
                placeholder="https://example.com"
                class="w-full px-4 py-1 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300"
            >

        </div>

        <!-- City / State -->

        <div>

            <label class="block mb-2 font-medium">

                City / State

            </label>

            <input
                id="location"
                type="text"
                maxlength="100"
                placeholder="Chennai, Tamil Nadu"
                class="w-full px-4 py-1 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300"
            >

        </div>

        <!-- Country -->

        <div>

            <label class="block mb-2 font-medium">

                Country

            </label>

            <select
                id="country"
                class="w-full px-4 py-1 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300"
            >

                <option value="">
                    Select Country
                </option>

            </select>

        </div>

    </div>


</fieldset>



<!-- Services & Skills -->
<fieldset>
    <legend>Services & Skills</legend>
    
        <div class="space-y-6">
    
            <!-- Services -->
    
            <div>
    
                <label class="block mb-2 font-medium">
    
                    Services
    
                </label>
    
                <textarea
                    id="services"
                    rows="3"
                    maxlength="500"
                    placeholder="SEO Consulting, Website Development, Graphic Design"
                    class="w-full px-4 py-1 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300 resize-y"
                ></textarea>
    
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">
    
                    Separate each service with a comma.
    
                </p>
    
            </div>
    
            <!-- Skills -->
    
            <div>
    
                <label class="block mb-2 font-medium">
    
                    Skills
    
                </label>
    
                <textarea
                    id="skills"
                    rows="3"
                    maxlength="500"
                    placeholder="SEO, Astro, JavaScript, Tailwind CSS"
                    class="w-full px-4 py-1 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300 resize-y"
                ></textarea>
    
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">
    
                    Separate each skill with a comma.
    
                </p>
    
            </div>
    
        </div>
    
    </fieldset>






<!-- Social & Professional Links -->
<fieldset>
<legend>Social & Professional Links</legend>

<div class="space-y-6">

    <!-- Facebook -->

    <div>

        <label class="block mb-2 font-medium">

            Facebook

        </label>

        <input
            id="facebook"
            type="url"
            maxlength="255"
            placeholder="https://facebook.com/username"
            class="w-full px-4 py-1 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300"
        >

    </div>

    <!-- LinkedIn -->

    <div>

        <label class="block mb-2 font-medium">

            LinkedIn

        </label>

        <input
            id="linkedin"
            type="url"
            maxlength="255"
            placeholder="https://linkedin.com/in/username"
            class="w-full px-4 py-1 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300"
        >

    </div>

    <!-- GitHub -->

    <div>

        <label class="block mb-2 font-medium">

            GitHub

        </label>

        <input
            id="github"
            type="url"
            maxlength="255"
            placeholder="https://github.com/username"
            class="w-full px-4 py-1 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300"
        >

    </div>

    <!-- YouTube -->

    <div>

        <label class="block mb-2 font-medium">

            YouTube

        </label>

        <input
            id="youtube"
            type="url"
            maxlength="255"
            placeholder="https://youtube.com/@channel"
            class="w-full px-4 py-1 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300"
        >

    </div>

    <!-- X -->

    <div class="md:col-span-2">

        <label class="block mb-2 font-medium">

            X (Twitter)

        </label>

        <input
            id="twitter"
            type="url"
            maxlength="255"
            placeholder="https://x.com/username"
            class="w-full px-4 py-1 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300"
        >

    </div>

</div>

</fieldset>



   



<!-- Promotional Links -->
<fieldset>
    <legend>Promotional Links</legend>

    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">

        Maximum 20 links

    </p>



    <input
        id="linkTitle"
        type="text"
        maxlength="100"
        placeholder="Link Title"
        class="px-4 py-1 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300 w-full mb-3"
    >

    <input
        id="linkUrl"
        type="url"
        maxlength="500"
        placeholder="https://..."
        class="px-4 py-1 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300 w-full"
    >




    <button
        id="addLinkBtn"
        type="button"
        class="btn bg-gray-500 w-full mt-3 border border-gray-500"
    >

        + Add Link

    </button>

<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-3">

    Promote your website, portfolio, products, blog, affiliate offers or other important pages.

</p>

<div
    id="linksList"
    class="mt-6 space-y-3"
>

    <div class="text-gray-500">

        No promotional links added.

    </div>

</div>

    </fieldset>
    






<!-- Sticky Action Bar -->

<div
    class="sticky bottom-0 z-40 bg-white border-t shadow-lg mt-10"
>

    <div
        class="bg-gray-100 max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 py-4 flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-between items-center gap-4"
    >

        <div>

            <span class="text-lead font-semibold">

                Manage Profile

            </span>

            <p
                id="saveStatus"
                class="text-sm text-gray-500"
            >

                Unsaved changes

            </p>

        </div>

        <div
            class="flex gap-3"
        >

            <button
                id="resetProfileBtn"
                type="button"
                class="btn-ol"
            >

                Reset

            </button>

            <button
                id="saveProfileBtn"
                type="button"
                class="btn"
            >

                Save Profile

            </button>

        </div>

    </div>

</div>

    
    </div>
    
</div>

<script is:inline type="module" src={`/assets/js/manage-profile.js?v=${version}`} defer></script>


<h2 id="delete-account">Delete Account</h2>    
<p>Members can delete their account and can create a new account at anytime. If you create a new account later, you'll be assigned the same user ID and each member's user ID is specific and unique to their respective email address. So, if you have shared your affiliate link anywhere, it still worth if you again create a new account later with the same email.</p>
<fieldset class="border-red-700">

    <legend class="text-red-900">

        Danger Zone

    </legend>

    <div class="space-y-4">

        <p>Warning! If you delete your account, all your profile data, configurations, website properties, affiliates, referrals, earnings, rewards, everything will be permenantly deleted. You can again create your account later anytime but, you'll start it from zero.</p>

        <button
            id="delete"
            class="
                btn bg-red-700 border-red-700 text-white float-right
            ">

            Delete Account

        </button>

    </div>

</fieldset>
</div>

<article class="prose lg:prose-xl max-w-none">

<h1>How to Maintain and keep Your Personal Branding Upated</h1>

<p>Your public profile represents you wherever you share it. Keeping it complete and up to date helps visitors understand who you are, what you offer, and how they can connect with you. A well-maintained profile also supports your marketing activities by presenting accurate information across every platform where your profile link is shared.</p>

<button class="w-full btn login go">
    Promote Your Personal Brand
  </button>

  <img  loading="lazy" src="/assets/images/others/manage-public-profile-wikimint-marketing-platform.webp" alt="Illustration of managing a public marketing profile with profile information, website links, social media, email marketing, analytics, and personal branding on the Wikimint Marketing Platform." title="Manage Your Public Profile | Wikimint Marketing Platform" class="w-full" />


<p>This page allows you to manage every important part of your profile from one place. Whether you want to update your description, change your website, add recommended links, or connect your social accounts, you can do it here without editing multiple pages.</p>

<h2>Create a Better First Impression</h2>

<p>People often decide within seconds whether they want to continue reading a profile. A complete profile makes that decision easier.</p>

<p>Your profile should clearly explain:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Who you are</li>
    <li>What you do</li>
    <li>Your professional interests</li>
    <li>Your business or website</li>
    <li>Ways to connect with you</li>
</ul>

<p>Keeping this information current helps visitors feel confident when interacting with your content.</p>

<h2>Write a Meaningful Profile Description</h2>
<h3>Tell Your Story Clearly</h3>

<p>Your profile description is one of the most important sections on your page. Use it to introduce yourself, explain your experience, and describe what visitors can expect.</p>

<p>Avoid writing only a few words. Instead, provide useful information that helps people understand your background and interests.</p>

<p>Updating your description regularly keeps your profile relevant as your business grows.</p>

<h2>Keep Your Website Information Current</h2>

<p>If your website changes, remember to update it here.</p>

<p>Your primary website often receives the most attention from visitors, so make sure it points to the page you want people to visit first.</p>

<p>Whether you promote a business website, blog, portfolio, or online store, keeping this link accurate improves the visitor experience.</p>

<h2>Organize Your Recommended Links</h2>
<h3>Share More Than One Resource</h3>

<p>Your recommended links section gives you the flexibility to promote several resources from a single profile.</p>

<p>You can organize links for:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Products</li>
    <li>Services</li>
    <li>Blogs</li>
    <li>Online tools</li>
    <li>Affiliate offers</li>
    <li>Educational resources</li>
</ul>

<p>Review these links from time to time and remove anything that is no longer useful.</p>

<h2>Connect Your Social Profiles</h2>

<p>Visitors often prefer following creators through social media before making future decisions.</p>

<p>Adding your important social accounts makes it easier for people to stay connected with your latest updates.</p>

<p>Keep only the profiles you actively use so visitors always reach your current accounts.</p>

<h2>Upload a Professional Profile Photo</h2>

<p>A clear profile photo helps visitors recognize you across different platforms.</p>

<p>Using the same photo on your website and social media accounts also creates consistency, making your online presence easier to remember.</p>

<h2>Review Your Profile Analytics</h2>
<h3>Learn From Visitor Activity</h3>

<p>Your dashboard provides useful information about your public profile.</p>

<p>Checking your analytics regularly helps you understand how visitors interact with your page and whether your updates are improving engagement.</p>

<p>Small improvements made over time often produce better long-term results.</p>

<h2>Prepare Your Profile Before Sharing</h2>

<p>Before sharing your profile link, take a few moments to review every section.</p>

<p>A quick checklist includes:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Profile photo</li>
    <li>Description</li>
    <li>Website</li>
    <li>Recommended links</li>
    <li>Social profiles</li>
    <li>Contact information</li>
</ul>

<p>A complete profile creates a better experience for every visitor.</p>

<h2>Keep Your Profile Active</h2>

<p>Your business changes over time, and your profile should change with it.</p>

<p>Whenever you launch a new website, publish a new product, change your business focus, or join another social platform, return here and update your profile.</p>

<p>An active profile helps visitors receive accurate information whenever they visit.</p>

<h2>Make Every Visit Count</h2>

<p>Your public profile can become one of the most valuable pages you own.</p>

<p>It brings together your personal introduction, website, recommendations, social profiles, and marketing opportunities in one location. Spending a few minutes updating your profile today can continue benefiting your online presence long after the changes are published.</p>

